<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-22-0486 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book is a comprehensive survey of the astrophysical characteristicsof the hot gas which pervades clusters of galaxies. The current theoreticaldescription of the origin, dynamics, and physical state of the clustergas is given. Observations by radio and optical telescopes are also summarised.The account is addressed to professional astronomers and to graduatestudents.</TEXT></DOC>